article.headline: Lehigh 63, Holy Cross 53
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 21 points to lead Lehigh past Holy Cross 63-53 Friday night. It was Lehigh's (12-7, 5-1 Patriot League) first win over Holy Cross (8-11, 2-4) since 2000. Strong defense and poor shooting led to a low-scoring first half, which ended with Holy Cross leading 23-22. Lehigh shot just 19 percent from the field in the first half; Holy Cross shot 32 percent. The Crusaders were led by Kevin Hamilton and Jave Meade with 12 points each. Kyle Neptune had 10 points for Lehigh, which shot 32 percent for the game. Austen Rowland was held to single digits for the first time in the last seven games. Lehigh went up by 13 with 8:18 remaining in the game. Holy Cross fouled often down the stretch, but Lehigh was 35 of 44 from the free throw line -- 80 percent. Holy Cross went to the line 24 times but converted just 13 -- 54 percent.
